ADDITIONAL TERMS AND CONDITIONS

1. Third-Party Services
   This software integrates with various third-party translation and speech
   services. Users are responsible for:
   - Obtaining their own API keys and credentials
   - Complying with the terms of service of each third-party provider
   - Managing costs associated with API usage
   
   Third-party services include but are not limited to:
   - OpenAI API (https://openai.com/api/)
   - Google Cloud Translation API (https://cloud.google.com/translate)
   - DeepL API (https://www.deepl.com/pro-api)
   - AWS Translate (https://aws.amazon.com/translate/)

2. Data Privacy
   This software processes potentially sensitive data including:
   - Voice recordings
   - Text translations
   - Meeting transcripts
   
   Users should ensure compliance with applicable privacy laws and regulations
   in their jurisdiction when using this software.

3. No Warranty for Translation Accuracy
   While this software facilitates translation between languages, the accuracy
   of translations depends on the third-party services used. The authors make
   no guarantees about the accuracy, reliability, or suitability of translations
   for any particular purpose.

4. Export Restrictions
   This software may be subject to export control laws and regulations. Users
   are responsible for compliance with all applicable export and re-export
   restrictions.

5. Contribution License
   By submitting contributions to this project, contributors agree to license
   their contributions under the same MIT License terms.

